Add Selection-Based Filter Widgets to Enable Users to Filter the Results

Selection-based filter widgets give users the ability to slice and dice the data to view results from different angles. For example, a list widget can filter results based on a particular case status or region.

Users viewing the dashboard can make selections in these types of widgets, which filter the results of other faceted widgets.

Add a Date Widget to Filter Dashboard Results Based on a Date
A date filter widget allows dashboard viewers to filter the CRM Analytics dashboard results based on a selected date range.
Add a List Widget to Filter Dashboard Results Based on a Dimension
A list filter widget allows dashboard viewers to filter the CRM Analytics dashboard results based on a dimension.
Add a Range Widget to Filter Dashboard Results Based on a Measure
A range widget allows dashboard viewers to filter the CRM Analytics dashboard results based on a range of values for a measure.
Add a Toggle Widget to Filter Dashboard Results Based on a Dimension
A toggle widget allows dashboard viewers to filter the CRM Analytics dashboard results based on a date or dimension.

You can create different types of selection-based filter widgets based on measure, date, and dimension fields. You can also set an initial selection for each of them.
